Wave 7: Phase 1.5 roadmap consolidation + system-prompt refresh

The development plan was last touched on 2026-04-17 and didn't reflect
Waves 0-6, even though the band was complete and pushed. The
system-prompt would have asked a regenerator to rebuild the original
Phase 1 only - missing every commercial-readiness feature shipped in
the autonomous Cursor band.

Wave 7 closes that documentation drift:

- docs/development-plan.md: new Phase 1.5 (Commercial-Readiness Band,
  Waves 0-6) added to the executive summary table AND as a new full
  section between Phase 1 and Phase 2. Cross-linked to ADRs 0013-0019.

- docs/status/shipped.md (NEW): per-wave delivery index. Each wave
  table-rows its deliverables with links to the ADR, runbook, ops
  script, defect card, and per-screen card. Includes the deliberate
  post-deploy feature-flag activation order so the operator's first
  prod window is repeatable.

- docs/system-prompt.md: §10.3 (public surfaces shipped in Wave 5),
  §10.4 (auditor-package export), iterator-coverage and
  production-bundle E2E expectations baked into §0 and §15. A
  regenerator now builds Wave 5-6 features from day one.

- CHANGELOG.md: Unreleased > Added entry for Wave 7.

qa:gate still PASS (66/66 routes, 52/52 API cells, 219/219 tRPC).
No code changes. Documentation only.
